<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The dictionary form is normally considered to be the form from which all others are derived. As
the @HI{{masu}} form is often introduced first, it can be useful to derive the dictionary form from it.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{five^grade}} verbs form the dictionary form by dropping @HI{{masu}} and
changing the final kana to the @HI{{u}}-row.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs form the dictionary form by dropping the final @HI{{masu}}
and adding the suffix @HI{{ru}}.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>

